git init karte hi default branch pehle master hoti thi or main hoti hai (Git version pe depend).
Default branch = master (old) / main (new).

rm -rf .git/ → Git repository ko completely delete kar deta hai (project normal folder ban jata hai).
Git hata deta hai (repo destroy).

git init --i(tab) kar dogh sida -> $ git init --initial-branch=
aajayega
git init --initial-branch=<name> → repo create karte time default branch ka naam change karta hai (master/main ke jagah).
Example:
git init --initial-branch=dev
Default branch name set karta hai.

cd testProject/ → terminal ka current directory testProject folder me change karta hai.
Folder ke andar le jaata hai.

mkdir testProject → testProject naam ka naya folder create karta hai.
New folder banata hai.

Ek hi project directory me git init karna kaafi hota hai, uske sub-folders me alag se Git repo banane ki zarurat nahi hoti.
Project root me hi Git init.
